    java.awt.event.ActionListener, java.awt.event.KeyListener, java.awt.image.ImageObserver, java.awt.ItemSelectable, java.awt.MenuContainer, java.io.Serializable, java.util.EventListener, javax.accessibility.Accessible, javax.swing.event.ListDataListener

    public class MyComboBox
extends javax.swing.JComboBox<java.lang.String>
implements java.awt.event.ActionListener, java.awt.event.KeyListener
    Custom implementaton of JComboBox to filter the dropdown list relative to the typed text.

    Supports a parent from which to read events and select the corresponding list.

    Author:
    Xavier Pe√±alosa

      • setAutocomplete

        public void setAutocomplete(java.lang.Boolean b)
        Calling this function with a true value will autocomplete the items in the JComboBox once a match is found with more than 4 characters.

        Calling this function with a false value will disable the automatic completion of the field.

        Parameters:
        b - - New value

      • initStrings

        Warning:

        Parameters:

      • updateSubstrings

        private void updateSubstrings()
        Add all the Strings that match the prefix typed in the JComboBox to the filtered ArrayList.

        Calls a binary search to find the first element that matches (start) and scans lineally until the string doesn't match.

        See Also:
        findStart(ComboBoxModel, String, int, int)
